  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "These findings underscore the need for continuous supervision and a critical and ethical use of ChatGPT to maximize its benefits in developing research competencies and minimize its risks in educational contexts.The results obtained in educational contexts reveal several significant findings that highlight both its advantages and challenges.",
    "The results show that the experimental group, which used ChatGPT, obtained higher scores in coherence, precision, and originality compared to the control group, suggesting that this tool facilitates a more coherent and precise presentation of ideas as well as greater creativity in content generation.",
    "This aligns with previous studies highlighting the utility of ChatGPT in higher education [25,26].However, we identified that the proper use of sources is an area where the control group outperformed the experimental group.",
    "This suggests that traditional research methods remain more effective in managing bibliographic references, highlighting a limitation of ChatGPT in this aspect [27,28].",
    "Moreover, although ChatGPT contributed to the generation of precise and relevant content, its effective implementation requires a critical approach to refine prompts and verify the accuracy of responses, aligning with the challenges mentioned in previous studies [40,41].In terms of developing research competencies, ChatGPT proved to be a valuable tool by enhancing students' coherence, originality, depth of content, and problem-solving abilities."
  ],
